Manuscript_Tree
===============
#Here are the commands I'm using to make the phylogeny for the Manuscript.

#First, connect the analysis lab computer via the ssh key. Then convert alignment files to phylip format.
python /usr/local/bin/convert_one_align_to_another.py ~/Desktop/PSG_Analyses/Percomorph_500 ~/Desktop/PSG_Analyses/Percomorph_500_Phylip/ \
--input-format nexus \
--output-format phylip \

#Then run CloudForest on the UCE phylip files to calculate the substitution models for each locus.
python /usr/local/bin/cloudforest_mpi.py ~/Desktop/PSG_Analyses/Percomorph_500_Phylip/ \
~/Desktop/PSG_Analyses/Percomorph_500_Cloudforest_Output/ \
genetrees \
/home/analysis/Downloads/PhyML-3.1/PhyML-3.1_linux64 \
--parallelism multiprocessing \
--cores 8

#Now, split the models from the genetree file.
python /usr/local/bin/split_models_from_genetrees.py \
~/Desktop/PSG_Analyses/Percomorph_500_Cloudforest_Output/genetrees.tre \
~/Desktop/PSG_Analyses/Percomorph_500_Cloudforest_Output/output_models.txt

#Create an input file that MrBayes can understand which incorporates the models and the nexus alignments.
python /usr/local/bin/format_nexus_files_for_mrbayes.py \
~/Desktop/PSG_Analyses/Percomorph_500 \
~/Desktop/PSG_Analyses/Percomorph_500_Cloudforest_Output/output_models.txt \
PSG_Analyses/MrBayes/mrbayes.nexus \
--interleave \
--unlink

#Now just run mrbayes!


